name: Transcon_GC_IC
description:
Transcon_GC_IC Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  one prepaid and 2 collect housebil traveling on DCT,ICT trough gateway  to its final destination
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/DEN
  Destination - QA1/YYC

  NOTE:

   While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
   In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
   In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:


  1. Run TRANSCON GC-IC_MCCOST automation script all the way through posting consol settlement at the destination
  Open correction at origin and update DC Origin Transfer amount by 10.00
  Add/Modify. Validate the suffix should be 03
  NEXT SCREEN-->Post DC
  Go to DCLOG at gateway and validate the contents especially all costs and charges fields for HB1 and HB2
  In command line enter MCCOST and DCANUM and click GO TO
  Validate the suffix and other contents. Suffix should be 03
  System should generate auto correction to IC. Validate contents and suffices for MCHBCS, MCCOST and MCTRAN for IC. Suffix should be 02

  2. Go to CFIT destination consol settlement screen and validate all fields including reason_Label field. Validate the suffix should be 02
  3. Grab and save master_invoice number for later use
  4. While in CFIT destination -->click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING
  5. Click on Option 11 AR History by Invoice
  6. Enter master_invoice# from step 3 in invoice_No field
  7. Click F7/SELECT INVOICE
  8. Validate all contents (NOTE: Invoice to service requesting branch)
  9. Grab and save E# from action1 line
  10. Click on action1 line and select F2/REVIEW INVOICE
  11. Validate all the contents
  12. Go to CFIT gateway-->Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING
  13. Click on Option 28 - Review Vendor Invoice
  14. Enter E# from action3 line from step 9 in vendor_Inv_No field and hit F2/FIND
  15. Validate all the contents (NOTE: payable to destination)
  16. Stay in CFIT gateway and go to the main page.
  17. click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING and Click on Option 11 AR History by Invoice
  18. Enter ICTNUM in invoice_No field and hit F7 (SELECT INVOICE) (NOTE: Invoice to origin)
  19. Validate all the contents
  20. Save all the E# (action1, action2 lines) under Event column. They are needed for later useValidate all content
  21. Log into EIFA gateway (QA4/MGR). In SELECTION_NO, enter 3 and hit Enter key. Again in SELECTION_NO, enter 1 and hit Enter key
  22. In JOURNAL field enter ICTNUM and hit Enter key
  23. Validate all fields in this screen including DISPLAY_REV_06 field. Hit Next Page and validate all fields ( NOTE: ES at gateway for IC after posting IC)
  24. Stay in EIFA gateway, Exit one time from the current screen to go back to the MENU_SCREEN #S1060.
  25. In SELECTION_NO, enter 1 and hit Enter key
  26. In JOURNAL field enter DCTNUM number and hit Enter key (NOTE: ES at gateway after posting DC destin cost)
  27. Validate all contents
  28. Go to CFIT origin -->Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING (NOTE: payable to gateway for the invoice sent in steps 16-19)
  29. Click on Option 28 - Review Vendor Invoice
  30. Enter E# from from step 20 in vendor_Inv_No field and hit F2/FIND. Need to do for each E#
  31. Validate all the contents
  32. Click EXIT button and repeat steps 28 and 29. Repeat for the rest of the E# saved from step 20
  33. Validate all the contents
  34. Go to CFIT Origin and click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTIN
  35. Click on Option 3 -->Pay from Invoice and enter DCTNUM in invoice_No field and hit F7/SELECT (NOTE: ES at origin after posting GC)
  36. validate all contents

  EHT1  prepaid  VRNYYC (Rate in local currency and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  EHT2  collect  VRN-YYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  EHT3  collect  DENYYC (Rate in local currency (USD) and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  DCT  VRN-DEN
  ICT  DEN-YYC
